"{\"uid\": \"news.cgtn.com-news-2024-05-28-Olympics-Chinese-weightlifter-Li-Fabin-eyes-more-glory-in-Paris-1tYjeplencY-p.html\", \"text\": \"Our Privacy Statement & Cookie Policy  By continuing to browse our site you agree to our use of cookies, revised Privacy Policy and Terms of Use. You can change your cookie settings through your browser.  Sports Scene  Copied  Chinese weightlifter Li Fabin is stepping up his preparations for the Paris Olympics, where he hopes to defend his title from Tokyo 2020.  During the Tokyo Games, the then debutant Li lifted a clean and jerk Olympic record of 172 kilograms in the men's 61-kg division on his second attempt.  Li Fabin of China competes in the men's weightlifting 61-kilogram division during the Asian Games in Hangzhou, China, September 30, 2023. /CFP  The Fujian native then clinched the gold medal with 313kg, also an Olympic record.  Two years later, Li bagged the World Championships and Asian Games titles to complete a career grand slam.  Li pocketed two more golds in the International Weightlifting Federation World Cup in Phuket, Thailand in April.  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466\"}"